HEADWORD: Minerva
<hw>Mi*ner"va</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<fld>(Rom. Myth.)</fld> <def>The goddess of wisdom, of war, of the arts
and sciences, of poetry, and of spinning and weaving; -- identified with
the Grecian <altname>Pallas Athene</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

